From: John Toomey <john.toomey@amd.com>
Date: Wed, 10 Dec 2025 08:32:35 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] boot: Re-enable console cursor after leaving boot menu

Upstream-Status: Submitted [https://github.com/systemd/systemd/issues/39292]

The menu_run() function disables the console cursor at entry via
ST->ConOut->EnableCursor(ST->ConOut, false) to hide it during menu
display, but never re-enables it when exiting. This leaves the cursor
permanently hidden after the boot menu closes.

This can cause the cursor to remain invisible when:
- Returning to the firmware (ACTION_QUIT)
- Booting an OS that expects the cursor to be in its default state
- Any subsequent text-mode console operations

Fix this by calling EnableCursor(true) before clearing the screen and
returning from menu_run(), restoring the cursor to its normal visible
state.

AI-Generated: Claude Opus 4.5

Signed-off-by: John Toomey <john.toomey@amd.com>
---
 src/boot/efi/boot.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/src/boot/efi/boot.c b/src/boot/efi/boot.c
index 5c0f0ab10a..c80ea7f395 100644
--- a/src/boot/efi/boot.c
+++ b/src/boot/efi/boot.c
@@ -1142,6 +1142,7 @@ static bool menu_run(
         }
 
         *chosen_entry = config->entries[idx_highlight];
+        ST->ConOut->EnableCursor(ST->ConOut, true);
         clear_screen(COLOR_NORMAL);
         return action == ACTION_RUN;
 }
